&lt;p&gt;If you are an experienced registered nurse (adult branch) looking for flexible, temporary work we can offer you the opportunity by joining the Staff Bank at Homerton University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to be confident that you have the skills to be responsible for delivering a high standard of nursing care. You will be an excellent communicator, with the ability to work using your own initiative as well as working effectively within a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Patient care is at the heart of what we do and you must be able to assess individual patient needs, plan to meet them and implement and evaluate the care planned. You must be able to adapt to work to meet the specific needs of patients and their relatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have the opportunity to work across the Trust in our acute medical, surgical and rehabilitation wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlbe ZamanJob titleBank Recruitment OfficerAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;huh-tr.bank.recruitment@nhs.net or call 0208 510 7604&lt;/p&gt;
